# ACCESSIBILITY

Message definitions for accessibility features provided by the Projection channel.
These messages allow querying the remote host's accessibility tree, subscribing to change events, and performing actions on UI elements.

The accessibility feature is useful not only for users with visual, auditory, or motor impairments, but also for LLM-based AI agents to structurally understand and interact with UI elements.
The accessibility tree provides a more efficient means of UI interpretation than directly analyzing video frames.

---

# CONSTANTS

## AccessibilityNodeRole

```constset
constset AccessibilityNodeRole: string {
  /// A readable text element.
  /// e.g., TextView (Android), Label (Windows), Text (macOS SwiftUI)
  const text = "text";

  /// A text field element that accepts user input.
  /// e.g., EditText (Android), TextBox (Windows), TextField (macOS SwiftUI)
  const textField = "textField";

  /// An image element.
  /// e.g., ImageView (Android), PictureBox (Windows), Image (macOS SwiftUI)
  const image = "image";

  /// A button element.
  /// e.g., Button (Android), Button (Windows), Button (macOS SwiftUI)
  const button = "button";

  /// A toggle button element (checkbox, radio button, etc.).
  /// e.g., CheckBox, RadioButton (Android), CheckBox, RadioButton (Windows), Toggle (macOS SwiftUI)
  const toggle = "toggle";

  /// A slider element.
  /// Scroll view scrollbars MAY also be represented as sliders.
  const slider = "slider";

  /// A combo box element (dropdown menu, etc.).
  /// e.g., Spinner (Android), ComboBox (Windows), Picker (macOS SwiftUI)
  const comboBox = "comboBox";

  /// A list element (list view, table view, etc.).
  /// e.g., ListView, RecyclerView (Android), ListView, DataGrid (Windows), List (macOS SwiftUI)
  const list = "list";

  /// A tab element (tab layout, etc.).
  /// e.g., TabLayout (Android), TabControl (Windows), TabView (macOS SwiftUI)
  const tab = "tab";

  /// A tree element (tree view, etc.).
  /// e.g., TreeView (Windows), OutlineGroup (macOS SwiftUI)
  const tree = "tree";

  /// A web DOM element. See the 'REPRESENTING DOM ELEMENTS' section below.
  const domElement = "domElement";

  /// A layout container element.
  /// e.g., LinearLayout, RelativeLayout (Android), StackPanel (Windows), VStack, HStack (macOS SwiftUI)
  const layoutContainer = "layoutContainer";

  /// A window element.
  const window = "window";

  /// An individual menu item element.
  const menuItem = "menuItem";

  /// A logical group of menu items.
  const menuGroup = "menuGroup";

  /// A menu container element.
  const menu = "menu";

  /// An application element.
  const application = "application";

  /// A display screen element.
  const display = "display";

  /// A GUI session element.
  const session = "session";
}
```

## AccessibilityNodeHint

```optionset
optionset AccessibilityNodeHint: uint32 {
  /// This node has interaction disabled. (disabled)
  option disabled = 0b1;

  /// This node is currently not visible. (invisible)
  option invisible = 0b10;

  /// This node is clickable.
  option clickable = 0b100;

  /// This node is scrollable.
  option scrollable = 0b1000;

  /// This node is focusable.
  option focusable = 0b10000;

  /// This node is focused.
  option focused = 0b100000;

  /// This node has additional content and MAY expand when the user interacts with it.
  option expandable = 0b1000000;

  /// This node is expanded.
  option expanded = 0b10000000;

  /// This node is selectable. (selectable)
  option selectable = 0b100000000;

  /// This node is selected. (selected)
  option selected = 0b1000000000;
}
```

## AccessibilityUpdateType

```optionset
optionset AccessibilityUpdateType: uint32 {
  /// Node properties (description, value, hint, etc.) have changed.
  option propertyChanged = 0x0001;

  /// Child nodes have been added, removed, or reordered.
  option childrenChanged = 0x0002;

  /// The node has been removed from the tree.
  option nodeRemoved = 0x0004;

  /// A new node has been added to the tree.
  option nodeAdded = 0x0008;
}
```

## GetAccessibilityTreeRequestFlags

```optionset
optionset GetAccessibilityTreeRequestFlags: uint32 {
  /// Include image snapshots of nodes.
  /// Snapshot generation consumes server resources, so this SHOULD NOT be overused.
  /// Depending on the server implementation, this flag MAY be ignored.
  option includeSnapshots = 0x0001;
}
```

## AccessibilityActionType

```constset
constset AccessibilityActionType: string {
  /// Performs the default interaction with the node.
  /// For example, this could be a click for a button, focus for a text field, or selection for a menu item.
  const activate = "activate";

  /// Deactivates the interaction with the node.
  /// For example, performing this action on a toggle button that is on MAY turn it off.
  const deactivate = "deactivate";

  /// Attempts to open a context menu from the node. Similar to a right-click action.
  const contextMenu = "contextMenu";

  /// Explicitly performs a 'click'.
  /// value: intval (optional) - mouse button index (0: left, 1: right, 2: middle)
  const click = "click";

  /// Explicitly performs a 'double click'.
  /// value: intval (optional) - mouse button index (0: left, 1: right, 2: middle)
  const doubleClick = "doubleClick";

  /// Explicitly performs a 'long press'.
  /// value: intval (optional) - mouse button index (0: left, 1: right, 2: middle)
  const longClick = "longClick";

  /// Focuses the node.
  const focus = "focus";

  /// Removes focus from the node.
  const blurFocus = "blurFocus";

  /// Scrolls the node.
  /// args: "deltaX" (optional) - horizontal scroll amount (negative for left, positive for right)
  ///       "deltaY" (optional) - vertical scroll amount (negative for up, positive for down)
  const scroll = "scroll";

  /// Expands the child content of the node.
  const expand = "expand";

  /// Collapses the child content of the node.
  const collapse = "collapse";

  /// Sets the value of the node.
  /// For example, this could be entering text in a text field or changing the value of a slider.
  const setValue = "setValue";
}
```

---

# STRUCTS

## AccessibilityNodeValue

```protobuf
/// Represents the value of an accessibility node.
message AccessibilityNodeValue {
  oneof value {
    string textValue = 1;
    bool boolValue = 2;
    int64 intValue = 3;
    float floatValue = 4;
  }
}
```

## AccessibilityNodeSnapshot

```protobuf
/// An image snapshot of a node.
message AccessibilityNodeSnapshot {
  /// MIME type of the image (e.g., "image/png")
  string mimeType = 1;
  /// Image data (binary)
  bytes data = 2;
}
```

## AccessibilityNode

```protobuf
/// Represents a node in the accessibility tree.
/// Each node has a unique ID and forms a tree through parent-child relationships.
message AccessibilityNode {
  /// Unique ID of the node
  SRUUID id = 1;

  /// ID of the parent node. Omitted for the root node.
  optional SRUUID parentId = 2;

  /// Role of the node
  // @constset: AccessibilityNodeRole
  string role = 3;

  /// State hints for the node
  // @optionset: AccessibilityNodeHint
  uint32 hint = 4;

  /// Position and size of the node on screen (relative to the top-left corner of the window, in pixels)
  SRRect bounds = 5;

  /// Position and size in the node's local coordinate system
  optional SRRect localBounds = 6;

  /// Human-readable description of the node
  string description = 7;

  /// Value of the node. For text elements this is textValue, for toggles this is boolValue, etc.
  optional AccessibilityNodeValue value = 8;

  /// Image snapshot of the node. Only provided when the includeSnapshots flag is set.
  optional AccessibilityNodeSnapshot snapshot = 12;

  /// HTML DOM attributes or GUI system-specific attributes.
  /// e.g., "dom.aria-label": "閉じる", "dom.disabled": "true"
  map<string, string> attributes = 13;

  /// Additional metadata for the client.
  /// Implementation-specific keys SHOULD use reverse domain name format.
  /// e.g., "app.noctiluca.x-display-id": "1", "app.noctiluca.x-bundle-id": "com.leaves.shizuku"
  map<string, string> metadata = 14;

  /// List of child nodes. MAY be omitted depending on the request.
  repeated AccessibilityNode children = 15;
}
```

### IMPLEMENTATION NOTES

- If `role` is a value not defined in `AccessibilityNodeRole`, it SHOULD be treated as a custom role in reverse domain name format. See the 'EXTENDING ROLES' section below.

---

# MESSAGES

## GetAccessibilityTreeRequest

```protobuf
/// Requests the accessibility tree.
// @opcode: 0x80E1
message GetAccessibilityTreeRequest {
  uint64 requestId = 1;

  /// ID of the node from which to retrieve the accessibility tree.
  /// The subtree rooted at this node will be returned.
  /// If omitted, the entire accessibility tree of the current GUI session is returned.
  optional SRUUID nodeId = 2;

  // @optionset: GetAccessibilityTreeRequestFlags
  uint32 flags = 16;
}
```

### DESCRIPTION

- Used by the client to request the accessibility tree from the server.
- The server MUST respond with a `GetAccessibilityTreeResponse`.

### IMPLEMENTATION NOTES

- Depending on the server implementation, a full tree request MAY be rejected. Access to specific nodes or windows MAY be restricted for security reasons.

## GetAccessibilityTreeResponse

```protobuf
/// Response to an accessibility tree request.
// @opcode: 0x80E2
message GetAccessibilityTreeResponse {
  uint64 requestId = 1;

  /// Whether the request was processed successfully. False if rejected.
  bool success = 2;

  /// Description of the rejection reason, if the request was rejected.
  optional string errorMessage = 3;

  /// The accessibility tree rooted at the requested node.
  /// This field MAY be empty if success is false.
  optional AccessibilityNode rootNode = 4;
}
```

### DESCRIPTION

- Response message for `GetAccessibilityTreeRequest`.
- If `success` is `false`, `rootNode` MAY be empty.

## SubscribeAccessibilityTreeUpdatesRequest

```protobuf
/// Requests subscription to accessibility tree update events.
// @opcode: 0x80E3
message SubscribeAccessibilityTreeUpdatesRequest {
  uint64 requestId = 1;

  /// ID of the root node of the subtree to subscribe to.
  /// If omitted, updates for the entire tree of the current GUI session are subscribed.
  optional SRUUID nodeId = 2;

  /// Event type mask to subscribe to.
  /// If 0x0000, all event types are subscribed.
  // @optionset: AccessibilityUpdateType
  uint32 eventMask = 3;

  /// Maximum depth of the subtree to subscribe to.
  /// If 0, all descendant nodes are subscribed without depth limit.
  /// If N > 0, only descendant nodes up to N levels from the specified node are subscribed.
  uint32 maxDepth = 4;

  // @optionset: GetAccessibilityTreeRequestFlags
  uint32 flags = 16;
}
```

### DESCRIPTION

- Used by the client to subscribe to change events on the accessibility tree.
- Specific event types MAY be filtered via the `eventMask` field.
- The subscription depth MAY be limited via the `maxDepth` field.

### IMPLEMENTATION NOTES

- Depending on the server implementation, subscription to the full tree MAY be rejected.
- For AI agent clients, it is RECOMMENDED to set `maxDepth` and `eventMask` appropriately to reduce unnecessary event traffic.

## SubscribeAccessibilityTreeUpdatesResponse

```protobuf
/// Response to a SubscribeAccessibilityTreeUpdatesRequest.
// @opcode: 0x80E4
message SubscribeAccessibilityTreeUpdatesResponse {
  uint64 requestId = 1;

  /// Subscription identifier. Used for receiving events and unsubscribing.
  SRUUID subscriptionId = 2;

  /// Whether the subscription was set up successfully. False if rejected.
  bool success = 3;

  /// Description of the rejection reason, if the subscription was rejected.
  optional string errorMessage = 4;
}
```

### DESCRIPTION

- Response message for `SubscribeAccessibilityTreeUpdatesRequest`.
- The `subscriptionId` is used when unsubscribing via `UnsubscribeAccessibilityTreeUpdatesRequest`.

## UnsubscribeAccessibilityTreeUpdatesRequest

```protobuf
/// Unsubscribes from accessibility tree update events.
// @opcode: 0x80E5
message UnsubscribeAccessibilityTreeUpdatesRequest {
  uint64 requestId = 1;

  /// Identifier of the subscription to cancel.
  SRUUID subscriptionId = 2;
}
```

### DESCRIPTION

- Cancels a previously registered accessibility tree update subscription.

## UnsubscribeAccessibilityTreeUpdatesResponse

```protobuf
/// Response to an UnsubscribeAccessibilityTreeUpdatesRequest.
// @opcode: 0x80E6
message UnsubscribeAccessibilityTreeUpdatesResponse {
  uint64 requestId = 1;

  /// Identifier of the cancelled subscription.
  SRUUID subscriptionId = 2;

  /// Whether the unsubscription was successful.
  bool isSuccess = 3;
}
```

### DESCRIPTION

- Response message for `UnsubscribeAccessibilityTreeUpdatesRequest`.

## AccessibilityTreeUpdateEvent

```protobuf
/// Accessibility tree change event.
// @opcode: 0x80E7
message AccessibilityTreeUpdateEvent {
  /// Subscription identifier.
  SRUUID subscriptionId = 1;

  /// Event type code.
  // @optionset: AccessibilityUpdateType
  uint32 eventType = 2;

  /// ID of the node targeted by this event.
  SRUUID nodeId = 3;

  /// Updated node information. This field is omitted for nodeRemoved events.
  optional AccessibilityNode updatedNode = 4;
}
```

### DESCRIPTION

- An event sent to subscribed clients to notify them of changes to the accessibility tree.
- This event is only received after subscribing via `SubscribeAccessibilityTreeUpdatesRequest`.

### IMPLEMENTATION NOTES

- For `nodeRemoved` events, `updatedNode` is omitted; the removed node is identified solely by `nodeId`.
- For `nodeAdded` and `propertyChanged` events, `updatedNode` contains the node state after the change.
- For `childrenChanged` events, `updatedNode` contains the parent node with its updated child list.

## DispatchActionRequest

```protobuf
/// Requests an action to be performed on an accessibility node.
// @opcode: 0x80E8
message DispatchActionRequest {
  uint64 requestId = 1;

  /// ID of the node on which to perform the action. (AccessibilityNode.id)
  SRUUID targetNodeId = 2;

  /// The type of action to perform.
  // @constset: AccessibilityActionType
  string actionType = 3;

  /// Additional value required for the action. e.g., textValue for text input, button index for click, etc.
  optional AccessibilityNodeValue value = 4;

  /// Additional arguments required for the action. e.g., "deltaX", "deltaY" for the scroll action.
  map<string, string> args = 5;
}
```

### DESCRIPTION

- Used by the client to request the server to perform an action on a specific UI node.
- The server MUST respond with a `DispatchActionResponse`.

## DispatchActionResponse

```protobuf
/// Response to a DispatchActionRequest.
// @opcode: 0x80E9
message DispatchActionResponse {
  uint64 requestId = 1;

  /// Whether the action was performed successfully.
  bool success = 2;

  /// Description of the failure reason, if the action failed.
  optional string errorMessage = 3;
}
```

### DESCRIPTION

- Response message for `DispatchActionRequest`.
- If `success` is `false`, `errorMessage` MAY contain the reason for failure.

---

# REPRESENTING DOM ELEMENTS

When representing a web browser's DOM element as an `AccessibilityNode`, set `role` to `domElement` and store DOM attributes in the `attributes` map with a `dom.` prefix.

For example, `<button aria-label="閉じる" disabled>閉じる</button>` is represented as follows:

```
attributes: {
  "dom.aria-label": "閉じる",
  "dom.disabled": "true"
}
```

---

# EXTENDING ROLES

When a role not defined in `AccessibilityNodeRole` is needed, a custom role MAY be defined using a string in reverse domain name format.

e.g., `com.leaves.shizuku.GameRendererView` — a view that renders the game screen of a text adventure game.

```
AccessibilityNode {
    id: "...",
    parentId: null,

    role: "com.leaves.shizuku.GameRendererView",

    description: "The school rooftop. Evening is approaching and the sunset is fading. A girl who introduced herself as Tsukiyama Shizuku is standing on the rooftop, gazing at the sunset.",
    children: [
        {
            role: "text",
            description: "Shizuku is watching the sunset. For some reason, she looks sad as she gazes at it. I...",
        },
        {
            role: "button",
            description: "A: Say to Shizuku, 'Let's head back now.'",
        },
        {
            role: "button",
            description: "B: Stand still, unable to do anything, just watching Shizuku.",
        }
    ]
}
```
